    {
      "id": "553f5d66de179096e981f3ff1484d25d3e2c8707",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-05-17 23:21:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 10: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(13 inline comments)\n\nI have no serious objection to the patch itself, but there are a lot of changes going on at the same time (moving CFS_ALLOC_ZERO flag to the callsites, adding the CPT allocators, renaming all of the cfs_page_{alloc,free}() functions) and this introduces a lot of room for getting something slightly wrong (e.g. missing CFS_ALLOC_ZERO somewhere, or getting the CFS_ALLOC_* flags wrong).\n\nAlso, I suspect that with the huge numbers of files/lines changed that there will be conflicts with some other patch repeatedly, making it difficult to land after testing and inspections have completed.\n\nIt might make sense to split this patch into a few smaller parts (e.g. add CFS_ALLOC_ZERO to callers maybe in a few patches, change primitives to use zalloc(), add CPT functions, etc), so that it is more likely to be able to land without conflicts.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "82774b96605d5507e45371cc8f6e8daf0e1259e9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-05-18 00:54:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\nI didn't realize that there will be other allocator patches when I submitted this one. But I agree that we can move many changes out from this patch and only keep the NUMA APIs.\nI will review other changes and make separate patch if necessary, or just drop if there is conflict with ongoing works. \n\nThanks\nLiang",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 10
    },
